node.text: Knowing how to edit is key!! 👏

You may not know about tiger shark vision👇🏼👀

Tiger sharks have pretty solid eyesight, especially in low light. Their eyes are built to pick up movement and contrast rather than fine details, and they have a reflective layer that helps them see better in dim conditions. 

While they might not see colours the way we do, they can spot silhouettes and changes in brightness, which is all they really need to track down their prey. Add in their ability to sense vibrations and electrical signals, and it’s no surprise they’re such efficient hunters! 

Their vision works alongside other senses, like their lateral line, which detects water movement, and electroreceptors that pick up the faint electrical signals of prey. While eyesight alone isn’t their primary hunting tool, it adds another layer to their ability to locate and ambush their prey with precision! 🦈
